    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "When thou beatest thine olive tree,.... With sticks and staves, to get off the olives when ripe: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "thou shall not go over the boughs again; to beat off some few that may remain; they were not nicely to examine the boughs over again, whether there were any left or not: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "it shall be for the stranger, for the fatherless, and for the widow; who might come into their oliveyards after the trees had been beaten, and gather what were left. ",
